        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35609",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=djvirgen",
                        "name": "djvirgen",
                        "displayName": "Hector Virgen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm putting together a patch that will allow registering custom helpers like this:\r\n\r\n\/\/ Adding a custom helper\r\n$view = new Zend_View();\r\n$helper = new MyCustomHelper();\r\n$view->addHelper($helper, 'foo');\r\n$view->foo(); \/\/ calls MyCustomHelper#foo()\r\n\r\n\/\/ Overwriting a built-in helper\r\n$myUrlHelper = new MyUrlHelper();\r\n$view->addHelper($myUrlHelper, 'url');\r\n$view->url(); \/\/ calls MyUrlHelper#url();\r\n\r\nAny thoughts on this?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=djvirgen",
                        "name": "djvirgen",
                        "displayName": "Hector Virgen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-29T10:02:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-29T10:02:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35610",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=blocka",
                        "name": "blocka",
                        "displayName": "Avi Block",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm wondering now if it's a good idea also to include anonymous functions here as well (a la Zend_Validate_Callback). Of course, one could always create a \"Callback\" helper this way as well, which would accomplish the same purpose, without having to change things around too much.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=blocka",
                        "name": "blocka",
                        "displayName": "Avi Block",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-29T10:07:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-29T10:07:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35611",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=djvirgen",
                        "name": "djvirgen",
                        "displayName": "Hector Virgen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What would that code look like? So far I have this:\r\n\r\n\/**\r\n * Registers a helper\r\n *\r\n * @param Zend_View_Helper_Abstract|object $helper\r\n * @param string $name\r\n * @return Zend_View_Abstract\r\n *\/\r\npublic function registerHelper($helper, $name)\r\n{\r\n    if (!is_object($helper)) {\r\n        throw new Zend_View_Exception('View helper must be an object.', $this);\r\n    }\r\n    $this->_helper[$name] = $helper;\r\n    return $this;\r\n}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=djvirgen",
                        "name": "djvirgen",
                        "displayName": "Hector Virgen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-29T10:30:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-29T10:30:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35612",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=djvirgen",
                        "name": "djvirgen",
                        "displayName": "Hector Virgen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sorry, forgot to add the code markup.. this should look better:\r\n\r\n{code:title=Zend_View_Abstract Patch (Draft)|borderStyle=solid}\r\n\/**\r\n * Registers a helper\r\n *\r\n * @param Zend_View_Helper_Abstract|object $helper\r\n * @param string $name\r\n * @return Zend_View_Abstract\r\n *\/\r\npublic function registerHelper($helper, $name)\r\n{\r\n    if (!is_object($helper)) {\r\n        throw new Zend_View_Exception('View helper must be an object.', $this);\r\n    }\r\n    $this->_helper[$name] = $helper;\r\n    return $this;\r\n}\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=djvirgen",
                        "name": "djvirgen",
                        "displayName": "Hector Virgen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-29T10:35:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-29T10:35:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35614",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=blocka",
                        "name": "blocka",
                        "displayName": "Avi Block",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What you have here seems to me to be sufficient for the main purpose of this feature (of course it must be tested!). As for adding in the anonymous function capabilities, you would probably have to change the __call method of Zend_View_Abstract, because that method is expecting a class and a method.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=blocka",
                        "name": "blocka",
                        "displayName": "Avi Block",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-29T10:51:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-29T10:51:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35615",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=djvirgen",
                        "name": "djvirgen",
                        "displayName": "Hector Virgen",
                        "active": true
